    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Instead of 'quitting' Facebook.]]></title>
    <link href="http://calumhalcrow.com/blog/2012/01/09/instead-of-quitting-facebook/"/>
    <updated>2012-01-09T08:49:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://calumhalcrow.com/blog/2012/01/09/instead-of-quitting-facebook</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>&hellip;just cut out a lot of the noise. Try taking the following steps:</p>

<!-- more -->


<ul>
<li>Unsubscribe from friends who get on your nerves.</li>
<li>Turn off notifications from any groups you like to be part of, but update often causing constant notifications.</li>
<li>Subscribe to &ldquo;important updates only&rdquo; from friends who you like to hear from but are a bit too chatty.</li>
<li>Block anything &ldquo;from Twitter&rdquo;.</li>
<li>Generally block/unsubscribe from any Group/Page that you like, but you don&rsquo;t need to hear from day to day.</li>
</ul>


<p>Suddenly your feed will be very quiet, and you&rsquo;ll find checking it once in a while will be a small pleasure rather than a constant catch-up reviewing posts that generally get on your nerves.</p>
]]></content>
